Manus,

I just got back from playing that game I was going to write an article about
-- you know, the one where people don't use strategies set in stone by
others? It's really really interesting - I saved all the orders and got each
player to write out their basic plans and aspirations each turn -- that was
REALLY interesting to read (especially people that were going to stab me!) I
played England. We only had 6 people so we put Italy in CD and played for 4
hours which got us to S1906. The final SC Count -

Turkey -11
England - 8
Austria - 8
France - 7
Russia - 0
Germany - 0

If the game had continued further, it would have been a Turkish/English
draw, probably, because I was killing France, my ally who (unsuccesfully)
stabbed me, and Turkey was really cutting down on his former ally, Austria.
Russia and Germany obviously got killed pretty quickly.

Anyway, I thought (and think) It would make for an interesting article.
Still interested?

Heath


